<HEAD>Chill Lingers Over North</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   An unseasonable cold wave lingered over much of the nation
today, bringing chilly temperatures from the Great Lakes region
through the Ohio and Tennessee valleys with freeze warnings posted
for Maryland and West Virginia.
   The freezing temperatures damaged some corn crops in St. Cloud,
Minn., and some farmers may have to replant, agriculture agent
Burton Olson said.
   Freeze and frost warnings were posted for extreme western
Maryland and for the northern and central mountains of West
Virginia.
   Much of the nation was dry Friday night and early this morning.
But showers and thunderstorms were widely scattered from western
and central parts of New Mexico through the east slopes of the
Colorado Rockies and Nebraska to eastern Montana and western North
Dakota.
   Showers and thunderstorms also were scattered across northern
Florida and the southern tip through the Florida Keys.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms along
southern Florida and central Colorado; and sunny skies over the
rest of the nation.
   High temperatures were forecast in the upper 60s and the 70s
from New England across northern Florida, from the Tennessee Valley
across New York, also along the northern Rockies and the Pacific
Coast; in the 90s from the northern half of the Plains, as well as
from central Texas across western Texas, New Mexico and western
Colorado; in the 90s to about 110 through the desert Southwest; in
the 80s over the rest of the nation.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 37
degrees at Bradford, Pa., to 91 degrees at Williston, N.D.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 61 fair; Boston 57 fair; Buffalo 49 cloudy;
Charleston, S.C. 55 fair; Cincinnati 44 fair; Cleveland 44 fair;
Detroit 52 fair; Miami 79 cloudy; New York 56 fair; Philadelphia 50
fair; Pittsburgh 44 fair; Portland, Me. 46 fair; Washington 56 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 75 fair; Chicago 55 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
65 fair; Denver 67 cloudy; Des Moines 58 fair; Indianapolis 53
fair; Kansas City 58 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 60 fair; Nashville
54 fair; New Orleans 70 fair; St. Louis 57 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 62 cloudy; Anchorage 52 cloudy; Las Vegas 73
fair; Los Angeles 57 fair; Phoenix 84 fair; Salt Lake City 62 fair;
San Diego 60 partly cloudy; San Francisco 55 partly cloudy; Seattle
52 partly cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 54 partly cloudy; Toronto 48 partly cloudy.
</TEXT>
