<HEAD>Tribesmen Keep Watch For Killer Wolf in Oman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MUSCAT, Oman (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tribesmen in a mountainous region of
northern Oman set up a round-the-clock watch for a wolf after the
remains of 6-year-old girl were found in a cave near their village,
newspapers reported Saturday.
   A goat shepherd found the remains of Miriam Toubiah, who had
been missing since March, in a cave 6,000 feet up Green Mountain.
   The village of Saiq, where the child lived, searched for her
after she disappeared. A witness reportedly heard a scream seconds
before she vanished.
   Villagers said a wild wolf made off with a child in a similar
incident three years ago. Although it is against the law to hunt
wildlife in Oman, the head sheik of Saiq received permission to
shoot wolves, the papers said.
