<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--ArcdeTriomphe     06-11 0143</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Arc de Triomphe,0144</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Huge Sheet To Hide Restoration Work On Arc de Triomphe</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mountain climbers will place a huge sheet over the
Arc de Triomphe to hide restoration work on the capital's beloved
monument.
   On Friday, 25 mountaineers will climb 165 feet to the top of the
arch to hang a 2,400-square-yard, red-white-and-blue canvas sheet
on one side of the monument.
   The first phase of work will take the entire day, organizers
said, with the other faces of the monument to be covered with
sheets in the following days.
   More than four tons of paint were used to cover the canvas in
the red, white and blue colors of the French flag.
   About $6 million will be spent to repair water and pollution
damage to the arch, which was constructed in 1806-1835 as a
monument to Napolean's armies.
