<HEAD>Arab World To Pay $42 Million Monthly To PLO, Paper Says</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUWAIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Arab leaders have promised to pay a monthly
subsidy of $42 million to support the activities of the Palestine
Liberation Organization, a Kuwaiti newspaper reported Saturday.
   The subsidy was adopted during a last week's summit of Arab
leaders, according to Al-Rai Aam.
   The newspaper said the payment is in addition to the $128
million in annual support the Persian Gulf nations earmarked for
