<HEAD>Eight-Year-Old Shooting Victim Released From Hospital</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Laurie Dann's Demons, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EVANSTON, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An 8-year-old girl who suffered the most
serious injuries among five children wounded in a shooting rampage
at an elementary school was released from the hospital Saturday,
officials said.
   Lindsay Fisher had suffered chest and abdominal wounds May 20
when Laurie Dann of neighboring Glencoe opened fire in Hubbard
Woods Elementary School in Winnetka.
   Eight-year-old Nicholas Corwin was killed, and Lindsay and four
other children were wounded. Ms. Dann, 30, also shot and wounded a
20-year-old man in a nearby home before fatally shooting herself as
police surrounded the house.
   Lindsay, hospitalized for three weeks, was the last of the
wounded to be released. She was moved out of Evanston Hospital's
intensive care ward May 26, and her condition was upgraded from
fair to good a day later.
   Riley McGee, the hospital's evening administrator, said she was
released Saturday.
